{
  "texts": [
    "Human performance remains consistent across sarcasm detection and agreement detection tasks, whereas the models show significant performance discrepancies in these tasks (with an average difference of 13%).",
    "Similarly, this gap is also observed in tasks concerning figurative language understanding with models showing an average gap of ∼ 25% and human performance only differs by 1%.",
    "In this section, we look into cases where LLMs fall short in simple pragmatic understanding tasks that humans do with ease.",
    "More specifically, we consider the LLaMA-2-70b base model due to its consistently high performance across various tasks and models.",
    "For implicature understanding, we see that the model fails to understand the meaning of the response when the response involves complex language phenomena like phrases, expressions, assumptions, or instances where common sense is needed, etc."
  ]
}